 that the company=E2=80=99s reputation s=
core among Republicans rose from 61 percent last year to nearly 68 percent =
in 2024, so the last thing C.E.O. Bob Iger wants to do is poke Trump with a=
 barbed Searchlight movie. Remember how Trump=E2=80=99s regulators held up =
AT&T=E2=80=99s acquisition of WarnerMedia for two years because he hated CN=
N=E2=80=99s coverage? Comcast C.E.O. Brian Roberts may soon go shopping for=
 Warner Bros. Discovery or Paramount Global. If Trump retakes the White Hou=
se, he may already punish the MSNBC owner=E2=80=94no reason to give him ano=
ther pain point. Many of the smaller distributors have
foreign money or are backed by billionaires with Trumpy politics, and the s=
treamers routinely censor content in territories and make pickup decisions =
with politics in mind. In 2018, Netflix won its first feature
Oscar for Icarus, about Russian doping. Last year, it declined to pick up t=
he sequel.

I know, politics isn=E2=80=99t the only reason for hesitation with The Appr=
entice. I haven=E2=80=99t seen it yet, but the reviews weren=E2=80=99t that=
 great, and it=E2=80=99s fair to wonder whether even art-house audiences wa=
nt to sit through this kind of story. The filmmakers have been adamant that=
 they want a release before the election, though I think they=E2=80=99d be =
flexible. Still, Trump fans will hate it if he tells them it=E2=80=99s bad,=
 and Trump haters can already see negative stories about him on the news ev=
ery night. We=E2=80=99ve all made up our minds on Trump, and he=E2=80=99s e=
verywhere all the time, so the appeal of an origin story may be limited, ev=
en with awards buzz. =E2=80=9CI think the strongest Oscar shot it=E2=80=99s=
 got is a supporting bid for Jeremy Strong,=E2=80=9D Kyle Buchanan, who cov=
ers the awards race for the Times and saw Apprentice in Cannes, texted me t=
his week when I
asked for his take. =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s great in it and Oscar voters who =
loved Succession will be excited they can finally vote for him.=E2=80=9D

True, but it=E2=80=99s not a sure thing=E2=80=94it=E2=80=99s not undeniable=
, to use Hollywood parlance that I hate. I do think the movie will find a h=
ome, albeit a smaller distributor. My point is someone should dive in here,=
 if only to give a platform to a movie people will talk about, and add a sp=
ark to this year=E2=80=99s awards season. =E2=80=9CIt would be tragic if co=
rporate distributors were too afraid to release a powerful film about the o=
rigins of our zero-sum, win-at-all-costs culture,=E2=80=9D Sherman emailed =
me. =E2=80=9CArt is meant to provoke. It=E2=80=99s what storytellers do.=E2=
=80=9D Can they still do it in Hollywood? Let=E2=80=99s see.

