ast for one day. I=E2=80=99m told <b>Elon Musk</b>=E2=80=99s platform forme=
rly known as Twitter is partnering with NewsNation, the Nexstar cable news =
channel that positions itself as offering =E2=80=9Cthe full range of perspe=
ctives,=E2=80=9D for what they=E2=80=99re gonna call =E2=80=9CThe People=E2=
=80=99s Town Hall.=E2=80=9D The plan is for questions from X users to be cu=
rated and posed to Trump via a Nexstar anchor and a prominent X user, and t=
he candidate=E2=80=99s responses will simulcast via the cable channel and a=
n X stream. <br/><br/><b>Linda Yaccarino</b>, the NBCUniversal ad sales gur=
u turned C.E.O.
of X, has been trying to insert the platform more directly into the electio=
n. She initially pitched the campaigns on an alternative debate format she =
dubbed =E2=80=9CThe People=E2=80=99s Debate.=E2=80=9D Trump said yes, and <=
b>R.F.K. Jr.</b> was in (of course), but the <b>Biden</b> camp balked. So n=
ow the president is out, the concept has been refashioned as a town hall, a=
nd Trump and R.F.K. will appear (separately) at a date T.B.D.</li><br/><li>=
<i>Paramount at the finish line</i>: <b>David Ellison</b>=E2=80=99s enhance=
d offer for Paramount and National Amusements is now in the hands of <b>Sha=
ri Redstone</b>. I=E2=80=99m told the special committee of Paramount board =
